I suspect this was probably one of the most enjoyable 24 hours of Scouting that people at our District are unlikely to experience again, so we are expecting to be invited back to again organise for this giant Jamboree, so we are asking any Leaders, Youth Members and Explorers to drop us an email if they would like any advanced notifications.

The following letters were written by my former Guider, and good friend, Wynter. They were written for an event Wynter that hosted along the following lines. We first called a meeting of our young people one Sunday Evening(August 2012) in our finished wood patio to study the nature of the world in front of us. “Senior Leader” type stuff, right? Even so, we invited and warmly welcomed all our youth through the evening, and security came and asked us to leave considering all the youth present :). After that first meeting, we decided to grow the group, and had breakfast meetings one morning a week for a few weeks to plan our Jamboree.
